<div class="setup-tabs">
  <button class="setup-tab active" onclick="showTab('linux')">Linux / macOS</button>
  <button class="setup-tab" onclick="showTab('windows')">Windows</button>
  <button class="setup-tab" onclick="showTab('api')">Direct API</button>
</div>

<div class="setup-panel active" id="tab-linux">
  <p class="setup-desc">Create a cron job that runs every 5 minutes to keep your IP updated.</p>
  <p class="form-label">1. Create the update script:</p>
  <div class="code-block">
    <button class="code-copy" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy</button>
    <pre>#!/bin/bash
# /usr/local/bin/ddns-update-{{ record.subdomain }}.sh

# Update IPv4 (auto-detected from outbound connection)
curl -s -4 "{{ updateUrl }}?key=YOUR_API_KEY&subdomain={{ fqdn }}&name=$(hostname)" >> /var/log/ddns.log 2>&1

# Update IPv6 (auto-detected from outbound connection)
curl -s -6 "{{ updateUrl }}?key=YOUR_API_KEY&subdomain={{ fqdn }}&name=$(hostname)" >> /var/log/ddns.log 2>&1</pre>
  </div>
  <p class="setup-desc mt-2" style="font-size:0.8125rem">The <code>-4</code> / <code>-6</code> flags force curl to connect over IPv4 or IPv6 so the server auto-detects and updates the correct record. The <code>name=$(hostname)</code> tags each update with the machine name for tracking in the dashboard. Omit lines for address families you don't have.</p>
  <p class="form-label mt-3">2. Make it executable:</p>
  <div class="code-block">
    <button class="code-copy" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy</button>
    <pre>chmod +x /usr/local/bin/ddns-update-{{ record.subdomain }}.sh</pre>
  </div>
  <p class="form-label mt-3">3. Add a cron job (every 5 minutes):</p>
  <div class="code-block">
    <button class="code-copy" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy</button>
    <pre>*/5 * * * * /usr/local/bin/ddns-update-{{ record.subdomain }}.sh</pre>
  </div>
  <p class="form-label mt-3">Or using systemd timer — create <code>/etc/systemd/system/ddns-{{ record.subdomain }}.service</code>:</p>
  <div class="code-block">
    <button class="code-copy" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy</button>
    <pre>[Unit]
Description=DDNS update for {{ fqdn }}

[Service]
Type=oneshot
ExecStart=/bin/bash -c 'curl -s -4 "{{ updateUrl }}?key=YOUR_API_KEY&subdomain={{ fqdn }}&name=$(hostname)" ; curl -s -6 "{{ updateUrl }}?key=YOUR_API_KEY&subdomain={{ fqdn }}&name=$(hostname)"'</pre>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="setup-panel" id="tab-windows">
  <p class="setup-desc">Use Windows Task Scheduler to run an update script every 5 minutes.</p>
  <p class="form-label">1. Create <code>C:\ddns\update-{{ record.subdomain }}.ps1</code>:</p>
  <div class="code-block">
    <button class="code-copy" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy</button>
    <pre># PowerShell DDNS Update Script
$url = "{{ updateUrl }}?key=YOUR_API_KEY&subdomain={{ fqdn }}&name=$env:COMPUTERNAME"
try {
    # Update IPv4
    $result4 = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri $url -Method Get
    Add-Content -Path "C:\ddns\ddns.log" -Value "$(Get-Date) IPv4: $result4"
} catch {
    Add-Content -Path "C:\ddns\ddns.log" -Value "$(Get-Date) IPv4 ERROR: $_"
}
try {
    # Update IPv6 (use ip6=YOUR_IPV6 to set a specific address)
    $result6 = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri "$url&ip6=YOUR_IPV6" -Method Get
    Add-Content -Path "C:\ddns\ddns.log" -Value "$(Get-Date) IPv6: $result6"
} catch {
    Add-Content -Path "C:\ddns\ddns.log" -Value "$(Get-Date) IPv6 ERROR: $_"
}</pre>
  </div>
  <p class="setup-desc mt-2" style="font-size:0.8125rem">The <code>$env:COMPUTERNAME</code> variable tags each update with the machine name so you can track which computer last updated the record. Use <code>&amp;ip6=YOUR_IPV6</code> to set a specific IPv6 address, or omit if you only need IPv4.</p>
  <p class="form-label mt-3">2. Register the scheduled task (run as Administrator):</p>
  <div class="code-block">
    <button class="code-copy" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy</button>
    <pre>$action = New-ScheduledTaskAction -Execute "PowerShell.exe" -Argument "-NonInteractive -File C:\ddns\update-{{ record.subdomain }}.ps1"
$trigger = New-ScheduledTaskTrigger -RepetitionInterval (New-TimeSpan -Minutes 5) -Once -At (Get-Date)
Register-ScheduledTask -TaskName "DDNS-{{ record.subdomain }}" -Action $action -Trigger $trigger -RunLevel Highest -Force</pre>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="setup-panel" id="tab-api">
  <p class="setup-desc">Make a GET request to update your IP. Omit <code>ip</code>/<code>ip6</code> to auto-detect from the connecting address.</p>
  <div class="code-block">
    <button class="code-copy" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy</button>
    <pre># Auto-detect IPv4 (connect over IPv4), tag with computer name
curl -4 "{{ updateUrl }}?key=YOUR_API_KEY&subdomain={{ fqdn }}&name=MyPC"

# Auto-detect IPv6 (connect over IPv6)
curl -6 "{{ updateUrl }}?key=YOUR_API_KEY&subdomain={{ fqdn }}&name=MyPC"

# Explicit addresses
curl "{{ updateUrl }}?key=YOUR_API_KEY&subdomain={{ fqdn }}&ip=1.2.3.4&ip6=2001:db8::1&name=MyPC"

# IPv4 only
curl "{{ updateUrl }}?key=YOUR_API_KEY&subdomain={{ fqdn }}&ip=1.2.3.4"

# IPv6 only
curl "{{ updateUrl }}?key=YOUR_API_KEY&subdomain={{ fqdn }}&ip6=2001:db8::1"</pre>
  </div>
  <p class="form-label mt-3">Parameters:</p>
  <table class="table table-sm mt-2">
    <tr><td class="mono">key</td><td>Your API key (required)</td></tr>
    <tr><td class="mono">subdomain</td><td>Full hostname, e.g. <code>{{ fqdn }}</code> (required)</td></tr>
    <tr><td class="mono">ip</td><td>IPv4 address to set; omit to auto-detect from connection</td></tr>
    <tr><td class="mono">ip6</td><td>IPv6 address to set; omit to auto-detect from connection</td></tr>
    <tr><td class="mono">name</td><td>Computer/device name for update history tracking (optional, max 64 chars)</td></tr>
  </table>
  <p class="form-label mt-3">Response codes:</p>
  <table class="table table-sm mt-2">
    <tr><td class="mono">good &lt;ip&gt;</td><td>IP updated successfully</td></tr>
    <tr><td class="mono">nochg &lt;ip&gt;</td><td>IP unchanged</td></tr>
    <tr><td class="mono">badauth</td><td>Invalid API key</td></tr>
    <tr><td class="mono">badip</td><td>Invalid IP address</td></tr>
    <tr><td class="mono">abuse</td><td>Rate limit exceeded</td></tr>
    <tr><td class="mono">disabled</td><td>Record is disabled</td></tr>
  </table>
</div>


